I suppose in a sense you are correct, though perhaps 'conquer' is not the right word. Elon Musk may have been the first to take humans to Mars, in co-operation with the ESA and NASA, but the actual colonisation of the Red Planet didn't take place until way after that. He may be remembered as the "Father of Mars", but it was the work of the "Mother of Mars", Victoria Eden, that led to the creation of the Homo martiensis who now populate Mars, and so in a way I suppose she could be considered to have been the one who 'conquered' Mars in the end. I hope that cleared up any confusion!
